Scripts for helping with updating and building X.org packages,
particularly for automation purposes.

Examples
--------
The following checks out current git head of the -ati driver and
generates a package, prompting for manually fixing up merge issues and
such as you go.

  ./auto-xorg-git -p xserver-xorg-video-ati

The following retrieves the current git head of libxrender from xorg
overwriting any existing checkout, and generates a package of it with
version <VERSION>-0ubuntu0bwh non-interactively, dropping all Debian
patches to sidestep merge conflicts.  This could be appropriate if
you're processing a large number of packages for testing purposes and
wish to do things completedly automatically:

  ./auto-xorg-git -Dfn -p libxrender -a 0ubuntu0bwh -r gutsy



Status
------
Examples that work:

auto-xorg-git -r hardy -d origin/debian-unstable -H hooks -p x11proto-dri2
auto-xorg-git -r hardy -t "~" -g -p libdrm
auto-xorg-git -r hardy -t "~" -g -H hooks -d origin/debian-unstable -p mesa

auto-xorg-git -p xorg-server -b server-1.5-branch
auto-xorg-git -p xserver-xorg-input-mouse -e 1
auto-xorg-git -p xserver-xorg-input-keyboard -e 1

auto-xorg-git -e 1 -r hardy -H hooks ati
auto-xorg-git -r hardy -d origin/debian-unstable -H hooks radeonhd
auto-xorg-git -e 1 -r hardy -d origin/debian-unstable -H hooks savage

Currently some issues:

auto-xorg-git -p xserver-xorg-input-synaptics -d origin/debian-unstable
auto-xorg-git -p xserver-xorg-input-evdev -H ../xorg-pkg-tools/hooks

